史上最严禁“野”令，效果如何有待观察2月24日下午，全国人大常委会表决通过关于全面禁止非法野生动物交易、革除滥食野生动物陋习、切实保障人民群众生命健康安全的决定（下称《决定》），自公布之日起施行。
The Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) passed a decision on banning all illegal wildlife trade, eliminating abuses of wildlife, and ensuring people's lives, health and safety (hereinafter referred to as the Decision) in the afternoon of February 24, taking effect from the day of promulgation.
北京大学保护生物学教授、自然保护与社会发展研究中心执行主任吕植对《中国慈善家》表示 ，“这相当于是一个紧急决定”。
"This is tantamount to an urgent decision," Lu Zhi, a professor of conservation biology at Peking University and executive director of the Nature Conservation and Social Development Research Center, told China Philanthropists.
鉴于全面修订野生动物保护法还需要一个过程，由全国人大常委会尽快通过一个专门决定十分必要。
A special decision by the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress is necessary, given that a comprehensive revision of wildlife laws will require a process.
在《野生动物保护法》修订前查漏补缺此次通过的决定聚焦滥食野生动物的突出问题，目的就是要在相关法律修改之前，及时、明确全面禁止食用野生动物，严厉打击非法野生动物交易，为维护公共卫生安全和生态安全、保障人民群众生命健康安全提供有力的立法保障。
The decision focuses on the serious problem of wild animals being eaten in a timely and clear manner before the relevant laws are amended. The decision aims to strictly crack down on the illegal wildlife trade and provide a strong legislative guarantee for public health and ecological safety, and safeguard people's lives, health and safety.
我国现行的《野生动物保护法》禁食的野生动物法律规范，仅限于国家重点保护野生动物和没有合法来源、未经检疫合格的其他保护类野生动物。
The current laws and regulations on wildlife under the current Wild Animals Protection Law are limited to the protection of wildlife under special state protection and other wild animals without lawful origin and without quarantine qualification.
吕植介绍，该法案将野生动物分为三大类：一是国家重点保护野生动物，二是地方重点和“三有”动物（即具有生态价值、科学价值和社会价值的动物），也称非国家重点国家保护野生动物。
The bill divides wildlife into three broad categories: first, the state protects wildlife under special state protection, and second, local key areas and animals with ecological, scientific and social value, also known as non-state key countries to protect wildlife.
其中，国家重点保护动物不允许食用，其他的则可以合法进入食品市场，前提是获得林业部门的捕捉、驯养、经营的许可，以及农业部门的检疫证明。
Among them, animals under special state protection are not allowed to be eaten, while others may enter the food market legally, provided that they have the permission of the forestry department to catch, domesticate and operate and the quarantine certificate of the agricultural sector.
第三类野生动物，即没在任何前述名单上的，进入市场和餐馆无需专门手续。
The third category of wild animals, that is, those not on any of the aforementioned lists, does not require special formalities to enter markets and restaurants.
《决定》在《野生动物保护法》的基础上，以全面禁止食用野生动物为导向，扩大法律调整范围，确立了全面禁止食用野生动物的制度。
The Decision expands the scope of legal adjustments and establishes a comprehensive ban on the consumption of wildlife on the basis of the Wild Animals Protection Law and aims at the complete prohibition of the consumption of wild animals.
该决定明确规定，凡野生动物保护法和其他有关法律禁止猎捕、交易、运输、食用野生动物的，必须严格禁止。
The decision clearly stipulates that wildlife protection laws and other relevant laws must strictly prohibit hunting, trading, transporting and consuming wildlife.
全面禁止食用国家保护的“有重要生态、科学、社会价值的陆生野生动物”以及其他陆生野生动物，包括人工繁育、人工饲养的陆生野生动物。
Land wildlife under state protection "terrestrial wildlife of important ecological, scientific and social value" and other terrestrial wildlife under state protection is comprehensively prohibited.
全面禁止以食用为目的猎捕、交易、运输在野外环境自然生长繁殖的陆生野生动物。
It is forbidden to hunt, trade or transport terrestrial wildlife that grows and propagates naturally in the wild for food purposes.
专家建议设置可食用白名单《决定》还规定了严厉惩治非法食用、交易野生动物的行为，堪称“史上最严”。
Experts have suggested the creation of an edible white list. The decision also provides for tougher penalties for illegal consumption and trading of wildlife.
对违反野生动物保护法和其他有关法律规定，猎捕、交易、运输、食用野生动物的，在现行法律规定基础上加重处罚。
Those who, in violation of the wildlife protection laws and other relevant laws and regulations, hunt, trade, transport or eat wild animals shall be given heavier punishments than those prescribed by the existing laws.
对本决定增加的非法食用和以食用为目的猎捕、交易、运输野生动物的行为，参照适用《野生动物保护法》等法律关于同类违法行为的处罚规定进行处罚。
The illegal consumption and hunting, trading and transporting of wildlife for food purposes as increased in this Decision shall be punished with reference to the provisions of the Law on the Protection of Wild Animals and other laws applicable to the same kind of illegal acts.
吕植认为，《决定》的作用也要拭目以待。
Lu Zhi believes that the role of the Decision also remains to be seen.
2016年修订的《野生动物保护法》在执行中存在着执法不到位的地方，比如执法信息不透明，检疫、市场监管缺失等。
The implementation of the Wildlife Protection Act, as amended in 2016, suffers from a lack of enforcement, such as lack of transparency in enforcement information, quarantine and lack of market regulation.
今年1月24日，吕植征集了19名来自全国高校、科研院所的学者、院士的联名签字，发布了《杜绝野生动物非法食用和交易，从源头控制重大公共健康危机》的倡议，并起草完成《从源头管理野生动物利用的具体建议》。
On January 24 this year, Lv Zhi collected 19 signatures by scholars and academicians from universities and research institutes across the country, issued an initiative entitled "Eliminating Illegal Consumption and Trade in Wild Animals and Controlling Major Public Health Crises at Source," and drafted the "Specific Recommendations for Managing Wildlife Utilization at Source."
吕植称，目前的《野生动物保护法》从生态保护的角度提得比较多，但对公共安全的考虑不足。
Lu said that the current "wildlife protection law" from the perspective of ecological protection more, but insufficient consideration for public safety.
从公共安全的角度，立法应该规范所有的野生动物利用。
From the point of view of public safety, legislation should regulate the use of all wildlife.
对于是否要全面禁止食用野生动物的社会争议，吕植认为反对者主要还是这个产业的利益相关者。
As for whether to ban the consumption of wild animals, Lu Zhi thinks the opponents are mainly stakeholders of the industry.
“其实经过这次疫情之后，大多数人应该应该不会再吃野生动物了。
"After the outbreak, most people should stop eating wild animals.
这个市场必然会萎缩，从业者应该看到这个趋势。
The market is bound to shrink, and practitioners should see the trend.
”吕植的建议是，《野生动物保护法》修订首先从理念上转变，建立白名单制，就是所有陆生脊椎野生动物都应该纳入野保法管理范围不允许食用，此外建立可食用动物名录。
Lu's proposal is for the wildlife law to be revised first conceptually to establish a white list system whereby all terrestrial wildlife in the spine should be included in the wildlife regulations and a list of edible animals should be established.
这与现行法律是两种相反的思路。
This is the opposite of the current law.
“这么做的一个根本原因是出于公共安全的考虑，因为病原体挑宿主时，并不会看它是不是重点保护野生动物。
"One of the fundamental reasons for this is public safety, because pathogens pick their hosts without looking at whether they are protecting wildlife."
”吕植说。
"said Lu.
对养殖户适当补偿在采访中，山水自然保护中心主任赵翔对《中国慈善家》表示，社会发展大方向肯定是禁食野生动物，但是对于《野生动物保护法》中的野生动物概念还要重新定义。
In an interview, Zhao Xiang, director of the Nature Conservation Center for Landscape Nature Conservation, told China Philanthropists that the general direction of social development must be a ban on wild animals, but the concept of wildlife contained in the Wildlife Conservation Law needs to be redefined.
目前深圳市的地方立法比较可取，具有参考意义。
At present, the local legislation of Shenzhen is preferable and has reference significance.
根据《深圳特区全面禁止食用野生动物条例（草案）》，深圳将全面禁止食用野生动物。
According to the Shenzhen Special Administrative Region Comprehensive Ban on the Consumption of Wild Animals (Draft), Shenzhen will ban the consumption of wild animals.
同时，条例也将制定颁布《深圳特区可食用动物名录》，并明确规定任何人不得食用或者组织食用《名录》以外的动物及制品。
At the same time, the Regulations will also formulate and promulgate the List of Edible Animals in the Shenzhen Special Administrative Region, and clearly stipulate that no one shall eat or organize the consumption of animals and products other than those on the List.
依据该草案，《深圳特区可食用动物名录》包括人工饲养的陆地动物猪、牛、羊、驴、兔、鸡、鸭、鹅、鸽、鹌鹑和法律、法规未禁止食用的水生动物。
The list of edible animals in the Shenzhen Special Administrative Region includes pigs, cows, sheep, donkeys, rabbits, chickens, ducks, geese, pigeons, quails and aquatic animals not prohibited by law and regulations.
全国人大通过的决定中也强调，鸽、兔等人工养殖、利用时间长、技术成熟，人民群众已广泛接受的人工饲养的动物属于家畜家禽，适用畜牧法的规定。
The decision adopted by the National People's Congress also stresses that farmed animals such as pigeons and rabbits, which have been farmed for a long time and are technically mature, and which have been widely accepted by the people, belong to livestock and poultry.
食用野生动物屡禁不止的背后，还存在着一个庞大的产业链。
There is still a huge industrial chain behind the repeated prohibition of eating wild animals.
据统计，2017年，陆生野生动物繁育与利用业的林产总值已达到560.351亿元。
According to statistics, the total value of forest products from the breeding and utilization of terrestrial wildlife reached 56,035.1 billion yuan in 2017.
吕植称，对于全面禁止食用野生动物，民间有较大共识。
Lu said that there is broad consensus among the people on the overall ban on eating wild animals.
目前反对的声音主要来自野生动物贸易的从业者和相关利益群体。
Opposition is coming mainly from wildlife trade practitioners and related interest groups.
“产业发展这么多年，背后有着盘根错节的利益链条。
"After all these years of industrial development, there is an interlocking chain of interests.
对于养殖户，尤其是一些贫困地区的农民群体其利益也可能受到影响，应扶持他们转型。
Farmers, especially in poor areas, whose interests may also be affected, should be supported in their transformation.
”吕植表示。
"said Mr Lu.
吕植建议，全面禁食野生动物后，针对养殖户的损失，可以效仿1998年国家停止天然林采伐后，政府以不同方式给予补贴扶持的方式解决。
Lu suggested that after a total ban on wild animals, the loss of farmers can be emulated in 1998 after the state stopped cutting natural forests, the government in different ways to provide subsidies to support the way.
